President Donald Trump met with survivors of the USS Arizona Pearl Harbor attack in the Oval Office. These World War II veterans, who were visiting Washington D.C. for the first time, paid tribute to those honored at Arlington National Cemetery and the memorials for World War II, Korea, and Vietnam. Trump praised the survivors for their courage and presented them with gifts, including a piece of the USS Arizona and a signed hat. The survivors also gave a bracelet to First Lady Melania Trump. After the meeting, they toured the White House. Trump expressed his admiration for the heroes and the strength of the nation.